VOICING PLAN:
- Verse 1 (bars 1-8): Light 2-note RH (open 5ths and 3rds), LH 3-4 notes open spacing.
  Primary patterns: "33" root position for I, V, IV. "43" 1st inversion for iii, vi.
- Verse 2 (bars 9-16): Similar to verse 1 but RH shifts register upward slightly.
- Refrain (bars 17-24): Fuller voicing, RH expands to 3 notes. 7th chords at DΔ7/C#ø7
  moments (bars 21-22). Final cadence converges to D root position.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bar 5-6 (DΔ7 → C#ø7 → D): The LH descends chromatically C#2→C#2→D2 through the
  half-diminished resolution, creating a smooth chromatic inner voice line.
- Bar 19: RH ascends G4→A4→B4 while LH holds the full G chord — contrary motion between
  hands at the sustained G measure.
- Bar 21: Climactic 3-note RH with full LH 4-note voicings at Bm/DΔ7/G, the
  richest texture of the arrangement.
- Bars 23-24: Cadential V→I with suspended A in LH held through the penultimate bar.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Bars 0-8 (verse 1): Sparse, 2-note RH + 3-note LH. Opens lightly.
- Bars 9-16 (verse 2): Similar density, slight upward shift in RH register.
- Bars 17-20 (refrain opening): 3-note RH begins to appear, 4-note LH throughout.
- Bars 21-24 (refrain close): Full 3-note RH, 4-note LH, widest range. Converges at final.
-->
